From c6165fa399c40a5616e357d53c7d5613865d8d8f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ram <chan2006@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 17:47:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add API key infrastructure + Brownfield auto-discover ingest
 endpoint
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First half of Brownfield auto-discover: lets a future/companion CLI
authenticate to ArchAI without a browser session, and submit
pre-structured resource data (from real cloud API calls) instead of
pasted Terraform.

- lib/api-keys.ts: generateApiKey()/hashApiKey(). Keys are
  archai_live_<48 hex chars>; only a SHA-256 hash is ever stored,
  the full key is returned once at creation and never retrievable
  again — standard practice for API keys.
- app/api/api-keys/route.ts + [id]/route.ts: create/list/revoke
  keys for the logged-in user. Revoke is a soft-delete (revoked_at
  timestamp) so usage history isn't lost.
- components/settings/SettingsClient.tsx: new 'API Keys' tab —
  generate a key (shown once, with a copy button and an explicit
  'won't be shown again' warning), list existing keys with
  prefix/created/last-used, revoke button. Fixed a set-state-in-effect
  lint issue by using the standard async-IIFE-in-effect pattern
  rather than calling a named async function directly from the
  effect body.
- app/api/brownfield/ingest/route.ts: new endpoint, authenticated
  via 'Authorization: Bearer <api_key>' instead of a session
  cookie. Accepts a pre-built ScanResult (same shape the Scanner
  agent already outputs from parsing pasted text) and target_cloud,
  skips the Scanner step entirely, then runs the exact same
  Auditor -> Planner -> Engineer -> ADR generation -> save pipeline
  as the pasted-input flow. Same Team+ plan gate applied.
- lib/supabase/middleware.ts: added the ingest route to the public
  allowlist, since it does its own API-key auth and would otherwise
  get redirected to /signin by the session-based middleware (which
  would break a CLI's POST request).

Needs a new Supabase table before this works — SQL provided
separately (create_api_keys_table.sql), same pattern as the earlier
RLS fix: run once in the SQL editor, no code deploy needed for it.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (26/26 pages,
all 3 new API routes confirmed in route table), no new lint errors
beyond the one pre-existing no-html-link-for-pages issue already
present in this file.

Note: this is backend infrastructure only. The actual CLI tool and
the Brownfield UI's 'Auto-discover' option are separate, following
commits.
